text:
Out of the blue: readers' photos on the theme of strange Share on Facebook Share on Twitter Share via Email View more sharing options Share on LinkedIn Share on Pinterest Share on Google+ Share on WhatsApp Share on Messenger Close 
For last week’s photography assignment in the Observer New Review we asked you to share your photos on the theme of strange via GuardianWitness . Here’s a selection of our favourites 

Share your photos on this week’s theme ‘together’ by clicking the button below Guardian readers and Tom Stevens 
Sunday 5 February 2017 09.00 GMT 
Bee shadow 
What is the shadow? It looks like a puppet, but zoom out and it’s clearly natural Photograph: DocPhil/GuardianWitness Facebook Twitter Pinterest 
Meeting in the Mist 
Photograph: mmmmbeer/GuardianWitness Facebook Twitter Pinterest 
Selfie-ish 
Photograph: RPGIBBS/GuardianWitness Facebook Twitter Pinterest 
Strange 
Surreal moment where a sand sculpture made from and and white plaster and natural black dye is consumed by the water. Amir the artist makes these every day by the hotels and asks for no money. At high tide they return to the sea Photograph: Colin Moody/GuardianWitness Facebook Twitter Pinterest 
A strange shower of umbrellas 
Encountered while cycling through France Photograph: John Parke/GuardianWitness Facebook Twitter Pinterest 
Strange face 
Statue seen in a museum Photograph: wickel/GuardianWitness Facebook Twitter Pinterest 
Sweet traffic lights 
Strange what goes through your mind when you have a blank sheet of paper and some sweets in front of you Photograph: klokan/GuardianWitness Facebook Twitter Pinterest 
Strange cat! 
Enough to scare the visitors away! Photograph: PMK052/GuardianWitness Facebook Twitter Pinterest 
Medusa 
Photograph: Jasmine Callen/GuardianWitness Facebook Twitter Pinterest 
Watching 
Photograph: Sara McCallum/GuardianWitness Facebook Twitter Pinterest 
Pom-pom flower 
Seen ‘growing’ on a platform at Crewkerne Station in Somerset Photograph: Caroline Collett/GuardianWitness Facebook Twitter Pinterest 
Cuban Grafitti 
Urban artwork on a wall in Havana Photograph: Salerio/GuardianWitness Facebook Twitter Pinterest 
I wasn’t expecting a voodoo temple 
Totally unexpected watering hole on the Makarska Riviera in Croatia. It was the end of season and the bar was shut for the winter. I’ll probably never know what goes on inside...Photograph: hogsvilleBrit/GuardianWitness Facebook Twitter Pinterest
